snippet.title: MEN are DYING! Scientist's Reveal Men's Y-CHROMOSOME is in DANGER
snippet.description:
Checkout Odoo to simplify your Business - https://www.odoo.com/r/Oum 

Humanity faces a significant threat: according to recent scientific research, men may be on the verge of extinction, with adverse effects on women as well. Recently, you may have heard reports, widely circulated in the news, about a serious illness affecting men at the DNA level, potentially leading to their disappearance.
A recent study from Kansas State University found that the genetic data of the Y chromosome, which is present only in males, is diminishing with each generation. This is alarming! But why is this happening only to men? Why arenâ€™t women experiencing similar changes in their genes? Interestingly, women's DNA is becoming stronger and healthier with each generation. So, does this mean life on Earth could end due to this male-specific decline? Is life fundamentally born with a fatal flaw? Could that flaw be death itself? Let's discuss...

Kaffara Episode 54 - [Eng Sub] - Ali Ansari - Laiba Khan - Zoya Nasir - 18th September 2024 - HAR PAL GEO

Sitara, a lively orphan living with her brother, aunt, and uncle, finds joy in life's small things despite her aunt's poor treatment. Her aunt keeps her around because she has a share in the family's property.
Salar, the son of a wealthy businessman, is passionate about photography, which often earns him criticism from his family. With a pure heart, Salar is known for evading his responsibilities.
At her cousin's wedding, Sitara wrongly assumes Salar is the photographer. Salar develops a soft spot for Sitara after seeing how poorly she is treated. However, due to a conspiracy, objections arise about their closeness. Salar, once again, avoids the issue, leaving Sitara to face doubts from her own family.
Can Sitara prove sheâ€™s not guilty? Will Salar help her avoid further mistreatment? Will her family support Sitara? Can Salar show he genuinely cares? Will there be more plots against Sitara?

snippet.title: Kya Kashmir Me Khilega Kamal? ft. Medha | Kashmir Elections | Jist
snippet.description:
In this compelling video, Jist reporter Medha travels across Anantnag, Pulwama, Baramulla, and other key areas in Kashmir to uncover the ground realities as the region prepares to vote after nearly a decade.

With the political landscape shifting dramatically, Medha highlights the significance of these elections in shaping the future of Jammu and Kashmir.

Anantnag, a stronghold of the PDP and the Mufti family, is witnessing fierce competition. 

Mehbooba Mufti's daughter, Sana, is contesting from Bijbehara while NC's Dr. Bashir Ahmad Veeri and BJP's Sofi Yousuf are also in the race. Medha captures the sentiments of local voters and the pressing issues they face.

Join us as we delve into the heart of Kashmirâ€™s electoral dynamics and explore how these elections could redefine political alliances and governance in the region. #KashmirElection #Article370 #JammuElection #NC #PDP #OmarAbdullah #Mehboobamufti #BJP #EngineerRashid

Kaffara Episode 53 - [Eng Sub] - Ali Ansari - Laiba Khan - Zoya Nasir - 18th September 2024 - HAR PAL GEO

Sitara, a lively orphan living with her brother, aunt, and uncle, finds joy in life's small things despite her aunt's poor treatment. Her aunt keeps her around because she has a share in the family's property.
Salar, the son of a wealthy businessman, is passionate about photography, which often earns him criticism from his family. With a pure heart, Salar is known for evading his responsibilities.
At her cousin's wedding, Sitara wrongly assumes Salar is the photographer. Salar develops a soft spot for Sitara after seeing how poorly she is treated. However, due to a conspiracy, objections arise about their closeness. Salar, once again, avoids the issue, leaving Sitara to face doubts from her own family.
Can Sitara prove sheâ€™s not guilty? Will Salar help her avoid further mistreatment? Will her family support Sitara? Can Salar show he genuinely cares? Will there be more plots against Sitara?

snippet.title: Mickey 17 | Official Trailer
snippet.description:
What's it feel like to die? From director Bong Joon Ho, comes Mickey 17 - only in theaters January 31, 2025. #Mickey17  

From the Academy Award-winning writer/director of â€œParasite,â€ Bong Joon Ho, comes his next groundbreaking cinematic experience, â€œMickey 17.â€ The unlikely hero, Mickey Barnes (Robert Pattinson) has found himself in the extraordinary circumstance of working for an employer who demands the ultimate commitment to the jobâ€¦ to die, for a living.

Written and directed by Bong Joon Ho, â€œMickey 17â€ stars Robert Pattinson (â€œThe Batman,â€ â€œTenetâ€), Naomi Ackie (â€œStar Wars: Episode IX â€“ The Rise of Skywalkerâ€), Steven Yeun (â€œNopeâ€), with Academy Award nominees Toni Collette (â€œHereditaryâ€), and Mark Ruffalo (â€œPoor Thingsâ€). 

The film is produced by Dede Gardner (Oscar winner for â€œMoonlight,â€ â€œ12 Years a Slaveâ€), Jeremy Kleiner (Oscar winner for â€œMoonlight,â€ â€œ12 Years a Slaveâ€), Bong Joon Ho and Dooho Choi (â€œOkja,â€ â€œSnowpiercerâ€). It is based on the novel Mickey 7 by Edward Ashton. The executive producers are Brad Pitt, Jesse Ehrman, Peter Dodd and Marianne Jenkins. The director of photography is Darius Khondji (Oscar nomination for â€œBardo: False Chronicle of a Handful of Truths,â€ â€œOkjaâ€). The production designer is Fiona Crombie (Oscar nomination for â€œThe Favourite,â€ â€œCruellaâ€). It is edited by Yang Jinmo (Oscar nomination for â€œParasite,â€ â€œOkjaâ€). The visual effects supervisor is Dan Glass (â€œFantastic Beasts: The Secrets of Dumbledore,â€ â€œFast & Furious Presents: Hobbs & Shawâ€). The costume designer is Catherine George (â€œOkja,â€ Snowpiercerâ€). 

Warner Bros. Pictures presents An Offscreen Production / A Kate Street Picture Company Production, A Film By Bong Joon Ho: â€œMickey 17.â€ The film will be distributed worldwide by Warner Bros. Pictures, in theaters only nationwide on January 31, 2025, and internationally beginning on 28 January 2025.

snippet.title: RED SNAPPER FISH | Big Fish Grill Recipe Cooking in Village | Fish Fry in Clay | Ancient Cooking
snippet.description:
Today in our village, we cook fish recipe using big red snapper fish. We grill this fish using clay. First, we apply the hand-ground traditional masala on the fish then we wrap it with banana leaf and silver foil paper and finally we cover the fish with clay. We directly grill the fish in the fire. 

Finally, we tasted the fish with a nice aroma! Tate is yummy!

#coconut  #climbing  #climbingmachine #innovation 

In this video, we showcase an innovative coconut plucking tool designed by Benin Lal Kingsley from Kanyakumari. With the growing challenges faced by farmers, such as labor shortages, this modern tool offers a practical solution. The tool's standout feature is that it allows coconuts to be plucked without needing to climb the tree, making the process safer and more efficient. This is an example of how new agricultural technologies are revolutionizing farming, providing much-needed relief to farmers and boosting productivity. Watch the video to see how this tool works and its potential benefits for coconut farmers.

snippet.title: Why 40% WORLD POPULATION Live in Only 2 Countries
snippet.description:
Checkout Odoo to simplify your Business - https://www.odoo.com/r/yQYN

In terms of population, India and China alone have more people than the combined total of all other 170 countries on Earth!  The world seems very crowded, and many experts suggest we need to control population growth. Even Elon Musk is talking about moving to Mars because of this issue.
However, if you look at the world population map, you'll see that most of the planet is still uninhabited. In Asia, India and China together house 2.7 billion people, or 36% of the worldâ€™s population. So, why do these two countries, located on the same continent, hold such a significant portion of the global population? Is their geographical location a key factor? Let's discuss.

Mangal Lakshmi unfolds as a poignant narrative, delving into the profound connection shared between two sisters, Mangal and Lakshmi. Set against life's myriad experiences, the story chronicles Mangal's odyssey in search of the ideal match, a 'dulha', for her cherished sibling, Lakshmi. As the tale progresses, it gracefully illustrates the intricacies of love, the resilience required to overcome trials, and the unwavering resolve that propels Mangal forward on her quest. Through the lens of sisterhood's enduring bond and the inexorable force of destiny, the narrative unfurls a tapestry of emotions, ultimately celebrating the timeless allure of fate in uniting kindred spirits.

Star Cast: Deepika Singh, Shubham Dipta, Naman Shaw, Upadhyay Urvashi,Vipul Tyagi
